      "created": "2012-12-04T17:48:05.695+0000",
      "description": "When a local disk becomes full, the node will fail every container launched on it because the container is unable to localize.  It tries to create an app-specific directory for each local and log directories.  If any of those directory creates fail (due to lack of free space) the container fails.\n\nIt would be nice if the node could continue to launch containers using the space available on other disks rather than failing all containers trying to launch on the node.\n\nThis is somewhat related to YARN-91 but is centered around the disk becoming full rather than the disk failing.",
      "priority": {
