          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12618756/comment/13919295",
            "id": "13919295",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sunilg",
              "name": "sunilg",
              "key": "sunilg",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Sunil G",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "May be NM can do some level of handling by itself in Disk Full scenario as in first place.\nNM's LocalDirAllocator gives a local path to write from the \"good\" list of directories.\nBut for this, it uses a round robin algorithm based on space available.\n\nIn a scenario like below, if more tasks asks for path from the set of local directories, \nthen it is possible that the allocation is done based on the current availability at that given time.\nBut this path would have earlier given to some other tasks to write and they may be sequentially doing writing.\n\nBasically the allotted space is not considered when next allocation is given for another task from same path. \n[Assuming few earlier allocated tasks is doing write at this time]\n\nBut it is not possible to consider this earlier allotted space and it is not possible to predict the disk write speed.\n\nCould it be possible to predict disk full scenario rather than acting on when it happens.\nFor Eg, current health check mechanism will check access permission etc to identify and good and bad directories for 2 minute interval.\nHere if the space is almost full (say 95% or only 5*100Mb is remaining), then it is better to move that directory to bad list directories.\n\nOr in the LocalDirAllocator, it is better to check for high percentage of disk used. And do not assign such a directory to that task.\nThese measures might possible help to resolve the new tasks not to fail because of an immediate disk full scenario.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=sunilg",
              "name": "sunilg",
              "key": "sunilg",
